<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-12-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-12-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="364" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d364">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 181.921/72</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Bandholtz</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Interallied Military
                            Mission</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Budapest</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-12-13">13 December, 1919</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Subject: Change of Status.</p>
                        <p>1. In compliance with telegraphic instructions from the American
                            Commission to Negotiate Peace, the undersigned this date ceases to be a
                            member of the Interallied Military Mission.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">H. H. Bandholtz</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>